---
import LegalLayout from "../layouts/LegalLayout.astro";

const lastUpdated = "May 8, 2026";
const effectiveDate = "May 8, 2026";

const sections = [
  { id: "acceptance", title: "1. Acceptance" },
  { id: "eligibility", title: "2. Eligibility" },
  { id: "license", title: "3. License" },
  { id: "accounts", title: "4. Accounts" },
  { id: "subscriptions", title: "5. Subscriptions" },
  { id: "ads", title: "6. Advertising" },
  { id: "user-content", title: "7. Your content" },
  { id: "acceptable-use", title: "8. Acceptable use" },
  { id: "ip", title: "9. Intellectual property" },
  { id: "third-party", title: "10. Third-party services" },
  { id: "disclaimer", title: "11. Disclaimer" },
  { id: "liability", title: "12. Limitation of liability" },
  { id: "indemnity", title: "13. Indemnity" },
  { id: "termination", title: "14. Termination" },
  { id: "law", title: "15. Governing law" },
  { id: "changes", title: "16. Changes" },
  { id: "contact", title: "17. Contact" },
];
---

<LegalLayout
  title="Terms of Service"
  description="The terms governing use of NexUtility's website and mobile applications."
  lastUpdated={lastUpdated}
  effectiveDate={effectiveDate}
  sections={sections}
>
  <p>
    These Terms of Service (the <strong>"Terms"</strong>) form a binding
    agreement between you and <strong>NexUtility</strong>
    (<strong>"NexUtility"</strong>, <strong>"we"</strong>, <strong>"us"</strong>)
    and govern your use of this website and any mobile application we publish
    on the Apple App Store or Google Play Store (the <strong>"Services"</strong>).
    These Terms incorporate our
    <a href="/privacy">Privacy Policy</a>.
  </p>

  <h2 id="acceptance">1. Acceptance</h2>
  <p>
    By installing, accessing, or using any of the Services you agree to these
    Terms. If you do not agree, do not install or use the Services.
  </p>

  <h2 id="eligibility">2. Eligibility</h2>
  <p>
    You must be at least 13 years old (or the higher minimum age required by
    your country) to use the Services. If you are under the age of majority,
    you may use the Services only with the consent of a parent or guardian who
    accepts these Terms on your behalf.
  </p>

  <h2 id="license">3. License</h2>
  <p>
    Subject to these Terms, NexUtility grants you a limited, personal,
    non-exclusive, non-transferable, revocable license to install and use the
    Services for your personal, non-commercial purposes. You may not copy,
    modify, redistribute, reverse engineer, decompile, or attempt to extract
    the source code of our apps except as expressly permitted by law.
  </p>

  <h2 id="accounts">4. Accounts</h2>
  <p>
    Most of our apps work without an account. If an app offers an account, you
    are responsible for keeping your credentials secret and for activity that
    occurs under your account. Tell us at
    <a href="mailto:support@nexutility.com">support@nexutility.com</a>
    immediately if you suspect unauthorized access.
  </p>

  <h2 id="subscriptions">5. Subscriptions, billing & refunds</h2>
  <p>
    Some of our apps offer optional subscriptions or one-time purchases.
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>
      <strong>Billing.</strong> All purchases are processed by Apple (App
      Store) or Google (Play Store). NexUtility never receives or stores your
      payment card details.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Auto-renewal.</strong> Subscriptions automatically renew at the
      end of each period at the then-current price unless cancelled at least 24
      hours before the end of the current period.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Free trials.</strong> Where a free trial is offered, it converts
      to a paid subscription unless cancelled before the trial ends.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Cancellation.</strong> You can cancel any time from your App
      Store or Google Play account settings. Cancellation stops future renewals
      and takes effect at the end of the current period.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Restore purchases.</strong> If you reinstall an app or switch
      devices, use the in-app "Restore purchases" option to re-enable an active
      subscription.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Refunds.</strong> Refunds are handled by Apple and Google
      according to their policies. We can help you find the right form at
      <a href="/support">/support</a>.
    </li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    Subscription entitlements are managed by RevenueCat on our behalf. The
    Apple Standard EULA does not apply where these Terms differ; in case of
    conflict between these Terms and the Apple Standard EULA, these Terms
    prevail to the maximum extent permitted by Apple's
    <a
      href="https://www.apple.com/legal/internet-services/itunes/dev/stdeula/"
      rel="noopener"
      target="_blank"
      >Licensed Application End User License Agreement</a
    >.
  </p>

  <h2 id="ads">6. Advertising</h2>
  <p>
    Some of our apps are supported by advertising delivered through Google
    AdMob. By using an ad-supported app you agree to receive ads. Where
    required by law or by Apple's App Tracking Transparency framework, we will
    ask for your consent before running personalized ads. If you decline, you
    will continue to see non-personalized ads.
  </p>

  <h2 id="user-content">7. Your content</h2>
  <p>
    You retain ownership of any content you create inside our apps
    (<strong>"User Content"</strong>). User Content is stored on your device by
    default. If an app provides cloud sync, you grant us a worldwide,
    non-exclusive, royalty-free license to host, transmit, and display that
    User Content solely to provide the sync feature to you. You are responsible
    for the content you create.
  </p>

  <h2 id="acceptable-use">8. Acceptable use</h2>
  <p>You agree not to:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Use the Services in violation of any applicable law.</li>
    <li>Reverse engineer, tamper with, or interfere with the Services.</li>
    <li>Use automated means to scrape, copy, or overload the Services.</li>
    <li>
      Attempt to circumvent ads, paywalls, license checks, or rate limits.
    </li>
    <li>Use the Services to infringe anyone else's rights.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="ip">9. Intellectual property</h2>
  <p>
    The Services, including their look-and-feel, source code, graphics, and
    "NexUtility" trademarks, are owned by NexUtility and its licensors and are
    protected by copyright, trademark, and other intellectual property laws. No
    rights are granted to you other than those expressly stated in these
    Terms.
  </p>

  <h2 id="third-party">10. Third-party services</h2>
  <p>
    The Services rely on third-party services (App Store, Play Store,
    Cloudflare, Google AdMob, RevenueCat). Your use of those services is
    subject to their own terms. We are not responsible for outages or actions
    of third-party services.
  </p>

  <h2 id="disclaimer">11. Disclaimer of warranties</h2>
  <p>
    THE SERVICES ARE PROVIDED <strong>"AS IS"</strong> AND
    <strong>"AS AVAILABLE"</strong> WITHOUT WARRANTIES OF ANY KIND, EXPRESS OR
    IMPLIED, INCLUDING BUT NOT LIMITED TO MERCHANTABILITY, FITNESS FOR A
    PARTICULAR PURPOSE, AND NON-INFRINGEMENT. WE DO NOT WARRANT THAT THE
    SERVICES WILL BE ERROR-FREE OR UNINTERRUPTED.
  </p>

  <h2 id="liability">12. Limitation of liability</h2>
  <p>
    TO THE MAXIMUM EXTENT PERMITTED BY LAW, NEXUTILITY WILL NOT BE LIABLE FOR
    INDIRECT, INCIDENTAL, SPECIAL, CONSEQUENTIAL, OR PUNITIVE DAMAGES, OR FOR
    LOST PROFITS, REVENUE, DATA, OR GOODWILL. OUR TOTAL LIABILITY ARISING OUT
    OF OR RELATING TO THESE TERMS OR THE SERVICES WILL NOT EXCEED THE AMOUNTS
    YOU PAID US IN THE 12 MONTHS BEFORE THE EVENT GIVING RISE TO THE CLAIM, OR
    USD 50, WHICHEVER IS GREATER.
  </p>

  <h2 id="indemnity">13. Indemnity</h2>
  <p>
    You agree to indemnify and hold harmless NexUtility against any claims
    arising from (a) your misuse of the Services, (b) your violation of these
    Terms, or (c) your violation of any third-party rights.
  </p>

  <h2 id="termination">14. Termination</h2>
  <p>
    You may stop using the Services at any time by uninstalling the app. We may
    suspend or terminate your access if you breach these Terms or use the
    Services in a way that endangers other users or our business. Sections that
    by their nature should survive termination (intellectual property,
    disclaimers, limitation of liability, indemnity, governing law) survive.
  </p>

  <h2 id="law">15. Governing law and disputes</h2>
  <p>
    These Terms are governed by the laws of <code>[Your jurisdiction]</code>,
    without regard to conflicts-of-law rules. Any dispute will be resolved in
    the courts of <code>[Your venue]</code>, except where mandatory
    consumer-protection law in your country grants you a different forum.
    Nothing in these Terms limits your statutory consumer rights.
  </p>

  <h2 id="changes">16. Changes</h2>
  <p>
    We may update these Terms occasionally. The "Last updated" date at the top
    will reflect the most recent revision. If a change is material, we will
    notify you in the affected app or via email. Continued use of the Services
    after changes take effect constitutes acceptance.
  </p>

  <h2 id="contact">17. Contact</h2>
  <p>
    NexUtility — <a href="mailto:legal@nexutility.com">legal@nexutility.com</a>.
  </p>

  <p class="!mt-12 rounded-md border border-warning/30 bg-warning/5 p-4 text-sm text-fg-muted">
    <strong>Note for the team:</strong> Replace bracketed values (governing
    jurisdiction, venue) and have these Terms reviewed by counsel before
    submitting any app for review.
  </p>
</LegalLayout>
